    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-27T04:13:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-27T04:13:00-05:00" n="301"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2158</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vladivostok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-27T18:00:00+08:47">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 27, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 28, 9.40 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. Your June 25, 5 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d301fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_224">p. 224</ref>.</note>
                    First, there are now 15,000 Czech troops here. Sixth, morale of troops is
                    splendid. Second, third, fourth, fifth, seventh, and eighth questions are being
                    answered by <persName corresp="#p_KAAM1">Admiral Knight</persName> in telegram
                    to Navy Department which is to furnish a copy to Department of State. <persName
                        corresp="#p_KAAM1">Admiral Knight</persName> is better able to answer
                    questions than I and his code is safer than mine.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJK1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
